I've heard this so many times from a small minority and it is always the same: total poppycock! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seriously, for a storyteller roleplayer, the fighting is not important and not required. Not required at all. If it is required by someone to be able to RP... then the RP is shallow. .. well ... it is not my sort of RP anyway. Futhermore, many of us hate PvP and the possiblities for having others enforce their 'roleplay' on you to actively ruin your session, with you having no option but to be the victim in THEIR story (even if you win, if you never wanted to fight at all) and not the protagonist of yours. If this server had been PvP .. I'd not be here, and neither would many others.<br>
<br>
PvP and RP are two very different things. If you haven't realized by now, learn it now: although some people love PvP AND love RP. and see them as natural partners, as you do, many others love RP but hate PvP. People like me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Perhaps that ogre player has to learn to more than one response to every situation.<br>
<br>
If you *really* feel this way, go to a Zek server. It is what they are for, people who love PvP. <p>------------------------------------------------<BR><BR>
